1. Hosts the processors, monitors, and Ethernet switches;
2. Acts as the central control unit for both the ES and EA subsystems; 
3. Supports ESM/ESU operations via EW systems;
4. Facilitates EA operations through RFPS and other EW systems;
5. Provides system health monitoring to the ES and EA subsystems.

1. It routes the 24VDC control voltage to the jammer unit; 
2. It enables jamming operations by providing power to the jammer unit; and 
3. It provides manual operation access for jammer initiation.

