2. Supporting the analysis of radar tracks to identify threat levels; and
3. Facilitating priority management based on identified risks.

1. Go to the 'ES Processor Menu';
2. Select 'Delete Warner Library';
3. Click on the menu item; and
4. The Warner Emitter Library is deleted from the ES Processor.

1. Go to the 'ES Processor Menu';
2. Select 'Load RFPS Library';
3. Clicking this item displays the RFPS Emitter Library; and
4. The user may view the library by clicking its name and delete the emitter from the RFPS Emitter Library if desired.

1. Access the 'Emitter Library Menu';
2. Select 'Delete Emitter Library Management';
3. Click the item to delete the emitter libraries;

1. Clicking the 'Get Statistics' button on the TFGD Pulse List retrieves the minimum, maximum, and mean values of frequency and pulse width;
2. A window pops up showing these statistics along with their associated error bars; and
3. Clicking the 'Get Intra Pulse Plot' button generates an image displaying the selected intra-pulse values and their error bars.
